WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.134
.

00:04.178 --> 00:06.571
- Previously,
on "Midnight, Texas"...

00:06.615 --> 00:08.312
- I failed you,
but I'll make it right.

00:08.356 --> 00:09.879
- I have something for you.

00:09.922 --> 00:11.533
It's supposed to protect you.

00:13.100 --> 00:14.362
- I saw you with Manfred.

00:14.405 --> 00:16.538
What could you possibly have
to say to him?

00:16.581 --> 00:18.235
You stay the hell away
from my wife!

00:18.279 --> 00:19.932
- I'll kill you!
- This isn't over.

00:19.976 --> 00:22.152
- Olivia, I feel
your every emotion

00:22.196 --> 00:24.111
as if it were my own.
- There has to be a way

00:24.154 --> 00:26.156
to sever this connection.
- Well, there is.

00:26.200 --> 00:28.506
If I turn you into a vampire.
- You really want

00:28.550 --> 00:31.292
to have that fight again?
- Can't do it!

00:31.335 --> 00:34.077
'Cause I love you.
[all hollering]

00:34.121 --> 00:37.037
- [groans]
- No, no, no.

00:37.080 --> 00:39.909
[heavy breathing]

00:39.952 --> 00:43.217
[dark music]

00:43.260 --> 00:45.523
- "Hexennacht"?
- It's German

00:45.567 --> 00:48.091
for "witch hell."
- Whatever you do,

00:48.135 --> 00:50.354
don't let them touch you.
- I'm not so sure

00:50.398 --> 00:53.314
about this, Feej.
Dark magic always has a price.

00:53.357 --> 00:55.664
- [laughing, growling]

00:55.707 --> 00:58.275
- Guys, Fiji's a dark witch.
She pulled a butterfly out

00:58.319 --> 00:59.711
of her chest and swore herself
to the dark side

00:59.755 --> 01:01.670
to save my hide.
- Come again?

01:01.713 --> 01:03.585
- Fiji discovered
that you're either a child

01:03.628 --> 01:06.370
of Delilah, a good witch,
or a child

01:06.414 --> 01:08.198
of Theophilus, a bad one.

01:08.242 --> 01:09.547
- Did you just say
"Theophilus"?

01:09.591 --> 01:11.506
- You should know,
he has a twin.

01:11.549 --> 01:13.638
Should the curse be broken,
they will regain

01:13.682 --> 01:15.466
their full power.
- And then what?

01:15.510 --> 01:17.729
- Darkness falls.
- Theophilus--

01:17.773 --> 01:19.731
it's Patience's twin.
She and her brother,

01:19.775 --> 01:22.343
they were cursed
by a dark witch--Delilah.

01:22.386 --> 01:25.389
- You don't get it.
Your wife lied to you.

01:25.433 --> 01:28.349
Theophilus is the father
of black magic!

01:28.392 --> 01:29.785
Together they'll be
the most powerful being

01:29.828 --> 01:33.049
to ever walk this Earth,
and it'll be your fault.

01:33.093 --> 01:34.659
- It belonged to Theophilus.

01:34.703 --> 01:37.619
It's like a--a binder
to fuse Theo's head

01:37.662 --> 01:39.229
to a host body.

01:39.273 --> 01:40.926
[whooshing]

01:40.970 --> 01:42.276
- [grunts]

01:44.278 --> 01:46.932
[grunting]

01:46.976 --> 01:49.587
That witch!
- Let go, let go.

01:49.631 --> 01:51.894
The more you pull on it,
the more it'll constrict.

01:51.937 --> 01:53.809
Just let go.

01:53.852 --> 01:56.420
[tense music]

01:56.464 --> 01:59.684
- Then how the hell
do I get it off?

01:59.728 --> 02:01.773
- I don't know.

02:01.817 --> 02:03.384
♪

02:03.427 --> 02:05.734
- So from day one
everything Patience did

02:05.777 --> 02:08.432
was just a long con.

02:08.476 --> 02:10.217
- How do you think I feel?

02:10.260 --> 02:12.393
I loved her.
I married her.

02:12.436 --> 02:14.438
Last 12 years of my life
have been a lie.

02:14.482 --> 02:15.831
- At least you get
to keep your head.

02:15.874 --> 02:18.094
- Not for long.
Once she has what she wants

02:18.138 --> 02:20.270
she'll kill us all.

02:20.314 --> 02:22.359
- Like she killed Creek.

02:22.403 --> 02:25.145
She didn't want me
to go to Austin with her.

02:25.188 --> 02:26.972
- Because she needed
your body.

02:27.016 --> 02:29.018
- I won't let her
get away with it.

02:29.061 --> 02:31.020
I'll kill her.
- [laughs]

02:31.063 --> 02:32.761
You can't.
She's immortal.

02:32.804 --> 02:34.241
- Well, then at least
I'll stop her

02:34.284 --> 02:35.938
from bringing her brother back.

02:35.981 --> 02:39.376
You said she needs me,
the vials, and the head.

02:39.420 --> 02:43.467
[tense music]

02:43.511 --> 02:45.252
Damn it.
Head's gone.

02:45.295 --> 02:51.823
♪

02:51.867 --> 02:54.913
- The vials are gone, too.
- We gotta warn everyone.

02:54.957 --> 02:57.786
♪

02:57.829 --> 02:59.614
Olivia!

02:59.657 --> 03:01.442
Lem! Bobo!

03:01.485 --> 03:08.666
♪

03:15.717 --> 03:17.458
- I--I'll keep searching
the hotel.

03:17.501 --> 03:19.547
- I'll look in the pawn shop.

03:20.896 --> 03:23.333
- Manfred?

03:26.031 --> 03:27.990
Are you okay, darling?

03:29.252 --> 03:31.863
You look a little spooked.
- Yeah.

03:31.907 --> 03:34.518
I, uh...
[scoffs]

03:34.562 --> 03:36.999
I--I got in a fight with Kai.

03:37.042 --> 03:38.870
He knocked me out.

03:38.914 --> 03:40.916
When I came to he was gone.

03:40.959 --> 03:43.135
He took the head and vials.

03:43.179 --> 03:46.313
Unless--unless you took them.

03:46.356 --> 03:49.011
Just please--
please just tell me

03:49.054 --> 03:50.708
you hid them.

03:50.752 --> 03:53.058
We can take them and--
and get as far away

03:53.102 --> 03:55.887
from Kai as possible.

03:55.931 --> 03:58.325
Oh, God, I--

03:58.368 --> 04:01.023
I was so worried about you.

04:03.112 --> 04:05.288
After Kai killed Creek I--

04:05.332 --> 04:07.464
I just need to know
you're okay.

04:07.508 --> 04:10.424
♪

04:10.467 --> 04:13.949
I love you.
[shaky breathing]

04:13.992 --> 04:18.214
♪

04:18.258 --> 04:20.564
- You know, don't you?

04:20.608 --> 04:22.914
[foreboding music]

04:22.958 --> 04:25.395
- Know what?

04:25.439 --> 04:27.658
- [foreign accent]
Drop it, Manfred.

04:27.702 --> 04:29.878
It's over.

04:29.921 --> 04:31.923
- [stammers, laughs]

04:31.967 --> 04:34.926
So the whole--the whole
"Southern charm" thing,

04:34.970 --> 04:37.538
that was--that was an act too?
- It seems we're both

04:37.581 --> 04:39.409
quite the thespians.

04:39.453 --> 04:40.802
And bravo.

04:40.845 --> 04:44.414
You almost had me--
until the "L-word."

04:44.458 --> 04:47.504
You don't love me any more
than I love you.

04:47.548 --> 04:50.855
- You want to chop my head off!
- It's nothing personal.

04:50.899 --> 04:53.945
Do you know how long
I've been trying to break

04:53.989 --> 04:55.599
this God-forsaken curse?

04:55.643 --> 04:58.559
That wretch Delilah
made it nearly impossible

04:58.602 --> 05:00.691
when she took away my powers.

05:00.735 --> 05:04.695
I mean, how am I supposed
to amass an army of beasts?

05:04.739 --> 05:08.743
But then it hit me:
I didn't need an army.

05:08.786 --> 05:10.310
Just Kai.

05:10.353 --> 05:12.877
A true healer
who could stockpile

05:12.921 --> 05:14.488
all their strength.

05:14.531 --> 05:15.967
- You came to Midnight

05:16.011 --> 05:19.623
and conned all
the supernaturals drawn here.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.756
- It was like shooting fish
in a barrel.

05:21.799 --> 05:24.149
- And I was your biggest catch.

05:24.193 --> 05:26.108
- Oh, you, my love,

05:26.151 --> 05:28.415
are icing on the cake.

05:29.503 --> 05:32.941
When Kai healed
your demon cancer

05:32.984 --> 05:35.639
and I saw the sheer amount
of garbage

05:35.683 --> 05:38.990
that came out of you...
- [rasping exhale]

05:39.034 --> 05:40.818
[eerie voices]

05:40.862 --> 05:44.039
- I knew that your body
could take in

05:44.082 --> 05:47.390
all 490 vials and live.

05:47.434 --> 05:50.872
You're the perfect vessel.

05:50.915 --> 05:54.702
And tomorrow night,
Theophilus' head

05:54.745 --> 05:57.487
will go on your body.
- [scoffs]

05:57.531 --> 05:59.620
I had Fiji perform
an intention spell.

05:59.663 --> 06:02.840
It said you were trustworthy.
- I created that spell.

06:02.884 --> 06:05.843
It can't work on me, lovie.

06:05.887 --> 06:07.889
[laughing]
- Manfred!

06:07.932 --> 06:09.847
Behind you!

06:09.891 --> 06:11.849
- What--what have you done
to them, Fiji?

06:11.893 --> 06:13.111
- Ah!

06:13.155 --> 06:15.070
Are you two besties now?

06:15.113 --> 06:17.159
I guess a threesome's
out of the question.

06:17.202 --> 06:18.552
- That's it!

06:18.595 --> 06:21.163
Damn it, Patience, you've--
- Ah-ah-ah-ah.

06:21.206 --> 06:23.687
- Fiji, don't.

06:23.731 --> 06:25.863
You've been conned
just like the rest of us.

06:25.907 --> 06:27.735
We're your friends,
not Patience.

06:27.778 --> 06:29.519
- Well, what Patience
is offering me

06:29.563 --> 06:32.348
is worth far more
than friendship.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.655
- [heavy breathing]

06:34.698 --> 06:36.874
[suspenseful music]

06:36.918 --> 06:41.183
[groaning]

06:41.226 --> 06:42.706
- Back off, witch.

06:42.750 --> 06:44.491
I just buried my husband.

06:44.534 --> 06:46.884
♪

06:46.928 --> 06:48.233
I'm warning you.

06:48.277 --> 06:52.542
♪

06:52.586 --> 06:54.326
- Where--where the hell
did they go?

06:54.370 --> 06:55.676
- They teleported.

06:55.719 --> 06:57.460
It's dangerous,
but witches will do it

06:57.504 --> 06:59.027
when they're desperate.

07:00.463 --> 07:02.204
- Yeah.

07:02.247 --> 07:03.771
They'll be back.

07:03.814 --> 07:06.991
[dramatic western music]

07:07.035 --> 07:08.993
♪

07:09.037 --> 07:11.387
[somber music]

07:11.431 --> 07:13.650
- He died in my arms.

07:13.694 --> 07:17.262
- You had no choice, Joe.
- No.

07:17.306 --> 07:18.786
No.

07:20.091 --> 07:21.832
I had a choice.

07:21.876 --> 07:24.269
If I hadn't been unfaithful
to Chuy none of this

07:24.313 --> 07:26.315
would have happened.

07:26.358 --> 07:28.491
- Oh, Joe.

07:28.535 --> 07:30.667
[sighs]

07:30.711 --> 07:32.103
I'm so sorry.

07:32.147 --> 07:34.932
- We know how much
you loved him.

07:34.976 --> 07:36.630
We all did.

07:36.673 --> 07:39.763
- We've all got a lot
to be sorry for.

07:39.807 --> 07:42.940
- Fiji went dark
trying to save me.

07:42.984 --> 07:45.552
- I mean, if I hadn't
brought Patience to Midnight...

07:46.814 --> 07:49.120
- [sighs]
Guys, feeling sorry

07:49.164 --> 07:52.472
for ourselves is not gonna
bring Creek back.

07:52.515 --> 07:54.996
[sighs]
Or Chuy.

07:55.866 --> 07:59.130
But maybe there's still hope
for Fiji.

07:59.174 --> 08:01.916
Look, what if we can get

08:01.959 --> 08:04.092
her butterfly back?
- We do that, then we have

08:04.135 --> 08:07.312
a powerful witch on our side.
- It's worth a shot.

08:07.356 --> 08:08.749
- All right.
in the mean time,

08:08.792 --> 08:10.490
we need to prepare
for their return.

08:10.533 --> 08:13.449
- Well, sun's coming up,
big guy.

08:13.493 --> 08:15.843
You've gotta sit
this rodeo out.

08:15.886 --> 08:18.933
- I'll be in the pawn shop,
in the dark.

08:18.976 --> 08:21.588
But we need to look
for more iron weapons.

08:21.631 --> 08:23.633
- Witch Kryptonite.
- And you need

08:23.677 --> 08:25.679
to get the hell out
of Midnight.

08:25.722 --> 08:27.507
- I'm not going anywhere.

08:27.550 --> 08:30.597
- If Patience gets her hands
on you, it's over for everyone.

08:30.640 --> 08:33.338
You need to leave.
- And go where?

08:33.382 --> 08:35.297
They're resourceful
and desperate.

08:35.340 --> 08:37.473
They'll find me eventually.

08:37.517 --> 08:40.650
It's safer here with them.

08:41.695 --> 08:43.610
We'll make our last stand here.

08:43.653 --> 08:45.699
Together.

08:45.742 --> 08:47.744
At midnight.

08:51.356 --> 08:51.531
.

08:51.574 --> 08:54.577
- When my brother returns
and I get my powers back,

08:54.621 --> 08:57.101
all my descendants
will be rewarded.

08:57.145 --> 09:00.278
Especially you, my sweet.

09:00.322 --> 09:02.585
But I need Manfred first.

09:02.629 --> 09:04.848
He's the key
to resurrecting Theophilus

09:04.892 --> 09:07.285
and your town of freaks
is in my way.

09:07.329 --> 09:08.939
- I know, they're so annoying.

09:08.983 --> 09:10.811
And when they're together
there's no stopping them.

09:10.854 --> 09:13.074
They will protect Manfred
at all costs.

09:13.117 --> 09:14.379
- What if he tries to run?

09:14.423 --> 09:16.425
- He'll never abandon
his friends.

09:16.468 --> 09:19.646
No, the only way
to get to Manfred

09:19.689 --> 09:23.475
is to take down the Midnighters
one by one.

09:23.519 --> 09:25.608
- Well, then we need to start
by getting rid

09:25.652 --> 09:29.394
of our biggest threat:
That bloody angel.

09:29.438 --> 09:32.354
We need a demon, Fiji.

09:32.397 --> 09:33.834
- Already on it.

09:36.184 --> 09:38.795
I call upon the power
of the East.

09:38.839 --> 09:42.930
Illuminate me
to find what I seek.

09:42.973 --> 09:50.198
♪

09:50.981 --> 09:53.636
[eerie breathing]

09:53.680 --> 09:55.333
- [chuckles]

09:55.377 --> 10:02.602
♪

10:05.692 --> 10:08.129
- [chuckles]

10:08.172 --> 10:11.088
♪

10:11.132 --> 10:12.786
- Follow me.

10:20.663 --> 10:23.492
- Well, the dagger you gave me
is made of iron.

10:23.535 --> 10:26.887
- Yeah. Let's see what else
we can find.

10:26.930 --> 10:33.197
♪

10:33.241 --> 10:34.546
- Joe!

10:34.590 --> 10:37.114
Your back!
- [sighs]

10:37.158 --> 10:38.681
Yeah, I, uh...

10:38.725 --> 10:41.684
cut off my wings.
- What?

10:41.728 --> 10:45.775
Your powers--are you now...?
- No, I'm still an angel, Lem.

10:45.819 --> 10:48.865
Can't change who I am.
- Why?

10:48.909 --> 10:50.867
- 'Cause I don't deserve them.

10:50.911 --> 10:54.044
I cut 'em off
for the sins I've committed.

10:54.088 --> 10:57.221
Penance for what I did to Chuy.

10:57.265 --> 10:59.441
- Joe...

10:59.484 --> 11:02.444
[somber music]

11:02.487 --> 11:06.883
♪

11:06.927 --> 11:10.887
We're all sinners,
and we've all fallen.

11:10.931 --> 11:13.847
But we get back up.

11:13.890 --> 11:16.371
♪

11:16.414 --> 11:17.981
- How long have you had
a camera in here?

11:18.025 --> 11:20.680
- Since the third time
you broke in.

11:20.723 --> 11:23.726
- [sighs]
I'm sorry.

11:25.119 --> 11:27.077
For everything.
[stammers]

11:27.121 --> 11:28.862
I was wrong about you.

11:30.515 --> 11:32.604
- I'm sure my wife helped
paint me as a villain.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.041
- Still, it was wrong.

11:34.084 --> 11:36.478
And so was my relationship
with Patience.

11:36.521 --> 11:38.393
I just--I thought
your relationship

11:38.436 --> 11:40.003
was on the rocks.

11:40.047 --> 11:42.310
Patience hinted that you were
having an affair.

11:42.353 --> 11:44.486
[both laugh]

11:45.879 --> 11:48.446
- I have the opportunity--
a lot--

11:48.490 --> 11:50.710
but I was faithful to my wife.

11:50.753 --> 11:53.451
Patience, she was
my everything.

11:54.539 --> 11:56.498
Speak of the she-devil:

11:58.587 --> 12:00.241
- Hey, what was that?

12:00.284 --> 12:01.590
Play that again.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.724
Look, there.
At the woman.

12:04.767 --> 12:07.030
She moved.

12:07.074 --> 12:09.076
Zoom in on that.

12:09.119 --> 12:10.730
[sinister music]

12:10.773 --> 12:12.514
I've seen that bracelet before.

12:12.557 --> 12:15.778
♪

12:15.822 --> 12:16.823
[energy rushing]

12:16.866 --> 12:18.041
[grunts]

12:19.216 --> 12:21.479
She--she beheaded Theophilus.

12:21.523 --> 12:22.785
♪

12:22.829 --> 12:24.352
- Well, then maybe
she can help.

12:24.395 --> 12:27.355
Can--can you make contact?
- [sighs]

12:27.398 --> 12:30.401
Well, if she's haunting
this painting...

12:30.445 --> 12:36.581
♪

12:39.846 --> 12:41.891
Yeah, I don't think
it's haunted.

12:41.935 --> 12:45.503
I'm not sensing any spirit.
- Uh, Manfred.

12:46.461 --> 12:49.638
[foreboding music]

12:49.681 --> 12:51.683
- Oh.

12:51.727 --> 12:52.989
- Wait, wait, wait.

12:53.033 --> 12:55.035
You think that's a good idea?
- Let me.

12:57.298 --> 13:00.257
[eerie chimes]

13:00.301 --> 13:03.565
♪

13:03.608 --> 13:06.568
[dramatic music]

13:06.611 --> 13:13.836
♪

13:17.100 --> 13:18.623
- Manfred.

13:22.845 --> 13:24.064
Manfred.

13:33.421 --> 13:36.076
[wind whistling]

13:39.601 --> 13:41.864
[eerie echoing whisper]

13:41.908 --> 13:44.040
- What the--?

13:44.084 --> 13:46.216
[distant roaring]

13:46.260 --> 13:48.436
[gasps]

13:48.479 --> 13:51.743
[approaching eerie rushing]

13:52.919 --> 13:55.095
[panting]

13:55.138 --> 13:57.924
[eerie whispering]

14:01.101 --> 14:02.842
[roaring]

14:02.885 --> 14:05.540
[gasps]

14:05.583 --> 14:07.324
What the hell was that?

14:07.368 --> 14:08.891
- A horrid thing

14:08.935 --> 14:11.589
put here to torture me
for all eternity.

14:11.633 --> 14:14.462
[both panting]

14:14.505 --> 14:16.725
Who are you?

14:16.768 --> 14:19.684
- My name's Manfred Bernardo.

14:19.728 --> 14:21.121
I need your help.

14:21.164 --> 14:23.819
- You reached out to me
from the other side.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.560
No one's ever done that before.

14:25.603 --> 14:28.258
Are you a wizard?

14:28.302 --> 14:29.520
- A medium.

14:29.564 --> 14:31.174
I-I thought you were a ghost.

14:31.218 --> 14:33.089
I can...
[sighs]

14:33.133 --> 14:35.526
I can make contact
with the spirit world.

14:35.570 --> 14:37.833
Other realms.
[panting]

14:37.877 --> 14:40.792
- That's how I was able
to bring you here.

14:40.836 --> 14:42.664
- Then you're the wizard.

14:44.274 --> 14:46.668
- A witch.

14:46.711 --> 14:48.931
One of the originals.

14:49.714 --> 14:52.021
Name's Delilah.

14:56.547 --> 14:56.765
.

14:56.808 --> 14:59.028
- If we want to get Fiji's
butterfly back, we'll need help

14:59.072 --> 15:00.203
from the Delilahs.

15:00.247 --> 15:02.597
But we have to be careful,
all right?

15:02.640 --> 15:06.209
Ask the wrong thing,
they'll block us.

15:06.253 --> 15:09.038
- Well, then we don't ask.

15:09.082 --> 15:11.388
[ambient music]

15:11.432 --> 15:13.260
Okay.

15:13.303 --> 15:17.351
♪

15:17.394 --> 15:20.136
[soft laugh]
I'm in.

15:20.180 --> 15:22.573
♪

15:22.617 --> 15:24.314
[static]

15:24.358 --> 15:26.751
- I'll take that.

15:26.795 --> 15:28.797
- Who the hell are you?
- Addie Wigget.

15:28.840 --> 15:30.668
I run IT
for Witches Helping Witches

15:30.712 --> 15:33.758
and hacking into our system
is a big no-no.

15:33.802 --> 15:35.064
Hand over the laptop, please.

15:35.108 --> 15:37.153
It is now the property
of the Delilahs.

15:38.546 --> 15:40.765
- That's cute.
- Whoa.

15:40.809 --> 15:43.072
[stammering]
We only hacked your site

15:43.116 --> 15:44.639
because we need your help.

15:44.682 --> 15:46.206
The love of my life,
she's in a heap of trouble.

15:46.249 --> 15:48.948
She's a witch--
her name is Fiji--and she made

15:48.991 --> 15:51.385
a terrible sacrifice
trying to save me.

15:51.428 --> 15:53.822
- She sent
her butterfly packing.

15:53.865 --> 15:56.912
- She removed her butterfly?
- And we need to get it back

15:56.956 --> 15:59.045
so she can help us
stop Theophilus.

15:59.088 --> 16:01.699
- Oh--did you just say
"Theophilus"?

16:01.743 --> 16:04.093
[inhaler hissing]

16:04.137 --> 16:06.791
- His twin is trying
to bring him back.

16:06.835 --> 16:08.706
- But Delilah put
an iron-clad curse

16:08.750 --> 16:10.839
on the father of darkness
800 years ago.

16:10.882 --> 16:12.928
What you're saying
is impossible.

16:14.321 --> 16:16.018
- The cage?
The head?

16:16.062 --> 16:18.803
His twin?
All here in Midnight.

16:18.847 --> 16:20.675
And if you don't help us
before they break the curse--

16:20.718 --> 16:22.459
- Then guess what?
We're all dead.

16:22.503 --> 16:24.722
- [groans]
- Oh, jeez.

16:24.766 --> 16:27.203
Hey, you all right?
You okay?

16:27.247 --> 16:29.640
- [sighs]

16:29.684 --> 16:32.121
- Been trapped in this hell
for centuries.

16:32.165 --> 16:33.993
- Well, I'm here
to break you out.

16:34.036 --> 16:36.734
My friends and I need
your help stopping Patience.

16:37.692 --> 16:40.303
- Theophilus' necklace.

16:40.347 --> 16:41.565
Oh, my God.

16:41.609 --> 16:43.132
Hypatia's close
to breaking the curse.

16:43.176 --> 16:45.656
- "Hypatia."
- That was her name

16:45.700 --> 16:47.354
when I knew her.

16:47.397 --> 16:48.616
[distant roaring]

16:48.659 --> 16:50.052
We must hide.

16:50.096 --> 16:51.227
Follow me.

16:58.104 --> 17:00.106
- [grunts]

17:00.149 --> 17:01.846
- We're safe.

17:01.890 --> 17:03.022
For now.

17:04.066 --> 17:06.851
If you're hungry,
I have possum.

17:06.895 --> 17:08.940
- Yeah, well, uh,

17:08.984 --> 17:12.727
I'm, uh--
I'm possum-intolerant.

17:14.685 --> 17:17.819
So, um, how'd you get trapped

17:17.862 --> 17:20.561
in the painting?
- It was Hypatia

17:20.604 --> 17:22.519
and Theophilus' doing.

17:22.563 --> 17:24.608
- Why?

17:24.652 --> 17:26.306
'Cause you're a--
you're a light witch

17:26.349 --> 17:28.047
and they're dark?

17:28.090 --> 17:31.572
- It wasn't always a light
and a dark.

17:32.747 --> 17:34.575
We weren't always enemies.

17:35.924 --> 17:38.579
- Oh, my God, she's doing it.
- Yeah!

17:38.622 --> 17:40.755
- [laughing]
- Almost.

17:40.798 --> 17:43.236
- Oh, my goodness.

17:43.279 --> 17:45.934
[all laughing]

17:45.977 --> 17:48.719
A brilliant use
of your talents.

17:48.763 --> 17:51.548
- Oh, well, who else
would I share my gifts with

17:51.592 --> 17:54.551
but the two of you?
[laughs]

17:54.595 --> 17:57.076
Ah.
[laughs]

17:57.119 --> 17:59.817
- Now, there's something
we'd like to share

17:59.861 --> 18:02.124
with you, sister.

18:02.168 --> 18:04.474
[peaceful music]

18:04.518 --> 18:06.868
- [clears throat]

18:06.911 --> 18:09.523
A gift from Theophilus.
[laughs]

18:09.566 --> 18:12.134
A sign of his intentions.

18:12.178 --> 18:14.223
[giggles]

18:14.267 --> 18:15.616
We're to wed.

18:15.659 --> 18:17.531
♪

18:17.574 --> 18:20.403
- I'm so happy for you both.

18:20.447 --> 18:23.624
[laughs]

18:23.667 --> 18:30.935
♪

18:38.508 --> 18:41.120
- I was betrayed
by my best friend.

18:41.163 --> 18:43.557
Just like your friends
betrayed you.

18:43.600 --> 18:45.124
- They're jealous
of my new power.

18:45.167 --> 18:47.300
- Ah, and Delilah was jealous
of the bond

18:47.343 --> 18:48.910
Theophilus and I had.

18:48.953 --> 18:51.913
So she came between us
and left me all alone.

18:51.956 --> 18:53.958
[weeping]
- Hypatia...

18:54.002 --> 18:56.961
- [sniffling, wailing]
- No one is taking me away.

18:57.005 --> 19:00.008
- [sobs]
- You'll always be my sister

19:00.051 --> 19:03.751
who I love with all my heart.
- [shaky breathing]

19:03.794 --> 19:07.189
- You love me with more
than your heart.

19:07.233 --> 19:09.757
[bitter music]

19:09.800 --> 19:12.325
I've seen the way
you look at me.

19:12.368 --> 19:13.978
With hunger in your eyes.

19:14.022 --> 19:18.200
- Stop it. It is forbidden.
We cannot act on it.

19:18.244 --> 19:21.769
♪

19:21.812 --> 19:24.772
[music sours]

19:24.815 --> 19:26.513
♪

19:26.556 --> 19:29.516
[both gasping]

19:29.559 --> 19:31.779
[dark music]

19:31.822 --> 19:33.694
- [gasps, moans]

19:33.737 --> 19:35.826
You felt that, didn't you?

19:35.870 --> 19:37.698
Didn't you feel that?

19:37.741 --> 19:40.701
I know you did, my love.

19:40.744 --> 19:42.311
♪

19:42.355 --> 19:44.618
- Never speak of it again.

19:44.661 --> 19:48.491
♪

19:48.535 --> 19:51.929
- That is messed up.

19:53.975 --> 19:57.283
- And I was with child.

20:00.547 --> 20:03.941
It should have been
the happiest time of my life...

20:05.247 --> 20:08.903
But I sensed Theophilus
pulling away...

20:10.383 --> 20:11.949
Because...

20:13.386 --> 20:16.345
because Hypatia
crossed a line.

20:16.389 --> 20:20.349
[mellow music]

20:20.393 --> 20:23.700
- A true vision...

20:23.744 --> 20:26.312
of beauty.

20:26.355 --> 20:33.406
♪

20:48.029 --> 20:50.988
[music grows dark]

20:51.032 --> 20:54.992
♪

20:57.299 --> 20:59.388
Hypatia, stop.

20:59.432 --> 21:02.696
No, no.
- Is that really what you want?

21:02.739 --> 21:05.699
[dark music]

21:05.742 --> 21:08.876
♪

21:08.919 --> 21:11.879
[eerie whispering]

21:11.922 --> 21:15.274
♪

21:15.317 --> 21:17.754
- Dark magic was born
that day.

21:17.798 --> 21:19.582
The magic you now embrace.

21:19.626 --> 21:22.716
Like Osiris and Isis,
like Zeus and Hera,

21:22.759 --> 21:24.674
we came together as one.

21:24.718 --> 21:26.197
Siblings and lovers.

21:26.241 --> 21:29.636
We gave ourselves over
to our desire.

21:29.679 --> 21:32.116
And released a force
that was not of this Earth.

21:32.160 --> 21:34.423
It was something powerful

21:34.467 --> 21:36.773
and beautiful.

21:36.817 --> 21:38.862
- It was an abomination.

21:38.906 --> 21:41.125
They took love...

21:41.169 --> 21:44.868
something pure and beautiful--
and corrupted it.

21:44.912 --> 21:47.610
Just as they did with magic.

21:47.654 --> 21:51.005
And vengeance filled my soul.

21:51.048 --> 21:54.835
- Patience took away
someone I loved too...

21:56.793 --> 21:59.970
And vengeance is all
I can think about.

22:01.624 --> 22:02.930
- I was heartbroken

22:02.973 --> 22:05.889
that I'd lost
Theophilus' love...

22:05.933 --> 22:09.545
but what came next
was so much worse.

22:11.852 --> 22:14.463
Hypatia, too, was with child,

22:14.507 --> 22:16.813
and the deeper
their perverse love grew,

22:16.857 --> 22:19.686
the more powerful they became.

22:19.729 --> 22:23.037
They surrendered
to the dark magic.

22:23.080 --> 22:25.996
With their evil sorcery,
they let loose a plague

22:26.040 --> 22:27.998
to kill those
that opposed them.

22:28.042 --> 22:30.827
[echoing screams]

22:30.871 --> 22:33.439
So I did the only thing
I could.

22:35.049 --> 22:38.095
[mellow music]

22:38.139 --> 22:45.276
♪

22:49.498 --> 22:51.065
- Delilah.

22:51.935 --> 22:54.155
- [screams]

22:54.198 --> 22:57.376
[dramatic music]

22:57.419 --> 23:04.383
♪

23:12.913 --> 23:14.915
I bind you both

23:14.958 --> 23:16.699
from all magic

23:16.743 --> 23:19.659
and curse your descendants
from ever experiencing love,

23:19.702 --> 23:22.531
as you have perverted it.

23:22.575 --> 23:26.448
- No!
[wailing]

23:26.492 --> 23:28.494
No!

23:28.537 --> 23:31.018
No!

23:31.061 --> 23:34.587
I found a way
to make her suffer, though.

23:34.630 --> 23:39.330
I couldn't practice magic
but our son, Everard, could.

23:39.374 --> 23:42.725
He cursed her, and trapped her

23:42.769 --> 23:45.467
in a painting for all time.

23:48.731 --> 23:50.864
- My vengeance came

23:50.907 --> 23:52.909
at such a cost,

23:52.953 --> 23:55.259
and it was all for naught.

23:55.303 --> 23:57.827
Hypatia and Theophilus
may soon be unleashed

23:57.871 --> 23:59.742
upon the world.

23:59.786 --> 24:02.571
[roaring]

24:02.615 --> 24:05.313
- [growls]

24:09.839 --> 24:10.057
.

24:10.100 --> 24:11.406
- [grunts]

24:11.450 --> 24:14.017
- [roaring]

24:14.061 --> 24:16.150
[dramatic music]

24:16.193 --> 24:19.849
♪

24:19.893 --> 24:21.590
- Run!

24:21.634 --> 24:24.463
- [roaring]
- [grunts]

24:24.506 --> 24:28.728
[shouting in foreign language]

24:32.471 --> 24:36.518
[roaring]

24:36.562 --> 24:38.520
[shouts]

24:38.564 --> 24:41.088
♪

24:41.131 --> 24:43.133
[camera shutter clicking]

24:43.177 --> 24:46.136
- [roaring]

24:46.180 --> 24:49.400
♪

24:49.444 --> 24:52.012
[snarling]

24:53.274 --> 24:56.799
[armor clattering]

24:56.843 --> 24:58.453
[grunts]

24:58.497 --> 24:59.933
[tense music]

24:59.976 --> 25:02.457
[panting]

25:02.501 --> 25:04.459
♪

25:04.503 --> 25:05.939
You okay?
[grunts]

25:05.982 --> 25:07.680
- Thank you.

25:08.681 --> 25:10.987
He's not gonna
bother you anymore.

25:11.031 --> 25:12.641
- For now.

25:12.685 --> 25:15.426
I've bested the Unholy Giant
a thousand times.

25:15.470 --> 25:17.341
He always comes back
to fight again.

25:17.385 --> 25:20.344
- I'll get you out of here.
- To do that, you need

25:20.388 --> 25:22.259
to break the spell,

25:22.303 --> 25:25.262
which is very difficult.

25:25.306 --> 25:28.004
You need to find the witch
who originally trapped me

25:28.048 --> 25:29.049
in this hell.

25:30.572 --> 25:33.140
- Patience's son.

25:33.183 --> 25:35.185
- Everard.

25:35.229 --> 25:38.449
- You--you get me back home,
I'll find him.

25:38.493 --> 25:41.104
♪

25:41.148 --> 25:44.368
- When I said we needed
a demon, I just assumed

25:44.412 --> 25:46.196
he'd be alive.

25:46.240 --> 25:49.504
How's Joe dead husband
going to help us?

25:49.548 --> 25:51.767
- Play on Joe's guilt.

25:51.811 --> 25:54.770
Now that this thing's dead,

25:54.814 --> 25:57.077
he's an even better weapon.

25:59.819 --> 26:03.736
[speaking foreign language]

26:06.347 --> 26:08.567
[whooshing]

26:08.610 --> 26:10.830
[gasps]

26:10.873 --> 26:14.050
[mellow music]

26:14.094 --> 26:18.228
♪

26:18.272 --> 26:20.491
- You okay?

26:20.535 --> 26:22.624
- I think so.

26:22.668 --> 26:24.800
- [sighs]
- Can you help us?

26:24.844 --> 26:26.715
♪

26:26.759 --> 26:28.412
- I don't know.

26:28.456 --> 26:31.720
Your girlfriend used
some really dark juju.

26:31.764 --> 26:33.809
When she removed her butterfly,

26:33.853 --> 26:35.724
she removed her soul.

26:35.768 --> 26:37.726
- Her soul.

26:37.770 --> 26:40.599
- [sighs]
- How can we get it back?

26:40.642 --> 26:43.427
- By finding Fiji's butterfly.

26:43.471 --> 26:46.996
But first we have to remove it
from where it's been hiding.

26:47.040 --> 26:49.999
It would have
magically taken refuge...

26:50.043 --> 26:53.524
in the person
that Fiji loved the most.

26:53.568 --> 26:56.615
♪

26:56.658 --> 26:57.964
- That's me.

27:00.444 --> 27:02.055
[inhaler hissing]

27:03.143 --> 27:05.580
- That's what I was afraid of.

27:05.624 --> 27:09.671
♪

27:09.715 --> 27:12.500
- [sighs]
We're done here.

27:12.543 --> 27:16.199
I think we've gathered every
witch-killing weapon we have

27:16.243 --> 27:18.288
in the shop.

27:18.332 --> 27:21.422
- This was actually used
in the Inquisition.

27:21.465 --> 27:24.207
Won't kill an immortal witch
like Patience, but it'll sure

27:24.251 --> 27:26.645
stop her in her tracks.

27:26.688 --> 27:27.950
- The sun's still up.

27:27.994 --> 27:29.778
I'd better wrap up
before heading out.

27:36.219 --> 27:38.613
[eerie whispering]

27:38.657 --> 27:41.616
[tense music]

27:41.660 --> 27:48.841
♪

27:53.715 --> 27:55.717
- Joe...

27:55.761 --> 28:02.942
♪

28:15.432 --> 28:18.392
[metal squeaking]

28:18.435 --> 28:21.830
[wind blowing]

28:21.874 --> 28:23.614
- Chuy?

28:23.658 --> 28:30.621
♪

28:30.665 --> 28:33.146
You're alive?

28:33.189 --> 28:34.495
How?

28:36.497 --> 28:38.673
- Why did you do this to me?

28:38.717 --> 28:40.980
- [shaky breathing]
I'm so sorry.

28:41.023 --> 28:44.200
[somber music]

28:44.244 --> 28:46.420
♪

28:46.463 --> 28:48.552
[whimpers]

28:48.596 --> 28:50.729
♪

28:50.772 --> 28:52.948
- [roars]
- [groans]

28:52.992 --> 28:55.646
[hollers]
- [growling]

28:55.690 --> 28:58.301
- [groans]

28:58.345 --> 29:01.217
[sinister music]

29:01.261 --> 29:03.437
[grunts]

29:03.480 --> 29:06.875
♪

29:06.919 --> 29:09.443
[groans]
- Mm-mm.

29:09.486 --> 29:12.228
[laughs]
- [groans]

29:12.272 --> 29:14.317
- It's over, Joe.

29:14.361 --> 29:17.886
- [groaning]

29:17.930 --> 29:19.975
- [laughing]

29:25.154 --> 29:25.546
.

29:25.589 --> 29:27.113
- Joe?

29:27.156 --> 29:29.985
- Why are the curtains down?

29:30.029 --> 29:32.988
[suspenseful music]

29:33.032 --> 29:33.989
- Joe?

29:34.033 --> 29:37.645
♪

29:37.688 --> 29:39.908
[whispered]
Joe.

29:39.952 --> 29:42.171
[groans]

29:42.215 --> 29:44.783
[grunts, chokes]

29:44.826 --> 29:45.784
[body thuds]

29:45.827 --> 29:48.787
- Sweet dreams.

29:48.830 --> 29:51.615
[laughing]

29:52.965 --> 29:56.316
- How can you be so sure
Everard is in witch hell?

29:56.359 --> 29:57.970
- He's the spawn
of black magic.

29:58.013 --> 30:00.537
Where else would he be?
- Look, I've never taken powers

30:00.581 --> 30:03.062
from a spirit before.
- When he crosses over

30:03.105 --> 30:04.628
he'll be as real
as you and me.

30:04.672 --> 30:07.283
That's why I'm trading places
with him on the other side.

30:07.327 --> 30:09.459
Remember what to do?
- Yeah.

30:09.503 --> 30:11.766
- All right.

30:11.810 --> 30:13.376
Do it quick.

30:15.117 --> 30:16.553
Hexennacht sucks.

30:17.859 --> 30:21.080
[speaking foreign language]

30:24.910 --> 30:26.868
Everard.

30:26.912 --> 30:28.304
♪

30:28.348 --> 30:30.437
Your mother is calling.

30:30.480 --> 30:33.440
[magical fire roaring]

30:33.483 --> 30:37.792
♪

30:37.836 --> 30:40.099
- [groans]
- Everard, your mother's

30:40.142 --> 30:41.143
in trouble.

30:41.187 --> 30:42.841
She needs your help.
Now.

30:42.884 --> 30:44.973
- Mother?

30:45.017 --> 30:47.889
♪

30:47.933 --> 30:49.325
Mother!

30:49.369 --> 30:51.545
Mother?

30:51.588 --> 30:54.504
[straining, groaning]

30:54.548 --> 30:57.464
[overlapping voices]

30:59.901 --> 31:01.772
- No.

31:01.816 --> 31:03.687
Damn it.

31:03.731 --> 31:06.908
[whispering voices]

31:06.952 --> 31:09.345
Come on, come on.

31:09.389 --> 31:11.391
[screaming]

31:11.434 --> 31:15.090
- [hissing]
- Really?

31:15.134 --> 31:17.397
Come on.

31:17.440 --> 31:21.923
♪

31:21.967 --> 31:24.360
[gasps]

31:24.404 --> 31:26.928
♪

31:26.972 --> 31:28.451
You get it?

31:28.495 --> 31:31.411
♪

31:31.454 --> 31:33.021
You bastard.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.938
- You have to follow
my instructions perfectly.

31:36.982 --> 31:39.985
If we want him to survive
we can't make any mistakes.

31:40.028 --> 31:41.029
[dubious music]

31:41.073 --> 31:43.031
We clear?

31:43.075 --> 31:44.903
[inhaler hisses]

31:44.946 --> 31:46.426
- Crystal.

31:46.469 --> 31:47.949
♪

31:47.993 --> 31:49.037
- We're gonna need that.

31:49.081 --> 31:52.606
♪

31:52.649 --> 31:55.957
[liquid squelching]

31:56.001 --> 31:57.698
[clears throat]

31:57.741 --> 32:00.440
- Um, what are you gonna do
with that creepy crawly?

32:00.483 --> 32:03.182
- Fiji's butterfly is safe
and warm inside you.

32:03.225 --> 32:05.532
It's not gonna want to leave.

32:05.575 --> 32:06.925
We're gonna have
to send something in

32:06.968 --> 32:09.449
to fish it out.
- Huh.

32:09.492 --> 32:11.146
♪

32:11.190 --> 32:14.628
That would explain this.
- Okay, put the hook in.

32:14.671 --> 32:16.064
♪

32:16.108 --> 32:19.111
Once the centipede finds
the butterfly,

32:19.154 --> 32:21.243
reel it out quickly.

32:21.287 --> 32:22.505
- Okay.

32:22.549 --> 32:25.378
You sure about this, Bobo?

32:25.421 --> 32:27.728
[loud exhale]
Fiji's pretty far gone.

32:27.771 --> 32:30.252
- I'm not giving up on her
no matter what.

32:30.296 --> 32:32.559
You understand?
- Okay.

32:32.602 --> 32:34.648
- Place it on Bobo's chest.

32:34.691 --> 32:36.780
♪

32:36.824 --> 32:40.306
- [heavy breathing]

32:40.349 --> 32:43.352
- [speaking foreign language]

32:43.396 --> 32:47.617
♪

32:47.661 --> 32:50.707
- [gagging, shouting]

32:50.751 --> 32:52.448
♪

32:52.492 --> 32:54.015
- Come on, Bobo.

32:54.059 --> 32:55.234
Come on.

32:55.277 --> 32:56.670
You got this.

32:56.713 --> 32:59.890
- [groaning]
- Now?

32:59.934 --> 33:01.980
- Wait.
- [gagging]

33:02.023 --> 33:03.894
[groaning, straining]
- Hold on, Bobo.

33:03.938 --> 33:06.985
It's killing him.
- Wait, wait, wait.

33:07.028 --> 33:09.596
- [stammering]
Come on, Bobo.

33:09.639 --> 33:11.032
All right, that's it.

33:11.076 --> 33:12.816
I'm pulling it out.
- Not yet!

33:12.860 --> 33:15.819
[centipede squealing]

